result.name: Wonderland Villas

reviews.text: A nice affluent location in the Kwai Chung district. Quiet, tranquil, if slightly remote.
Supreme night view. A very quiet and lovely place to live. It is like a hidden gem in Hong Kong

Great place to live. Outsiders will tell you how far away and remote Wonderland Villas is, but for residents, that means its quieter and takes you away from the hustle and bustle of the city. The flats are over 30 years old, but that means the layout is much more pleasant and space-efficient than modern flats. Word of warning, it does get very foggy up here and the temperature is a few degrees colder than the city during winter. My fingers are going numb as I type on my keyboard.

Nice place to live, quiet, surrounded by forest on the top of a hill with nice view. Good facilities: two swimming pools, gym with Wi-Fi, three tennis courts, study room, playground and lots of parking. Would be perfect to have a barbecue area ;)
High-class housing villa on the hill.
